The paper discusses the concept of interpretability in machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Given the focus on interpretability, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CE and cs.CR, which deal with the ethical and security implications of machine learning, respectively. Finally, cs.HC is also a possible sub-category as it deals with the human factors involved in interpreting machine learning models.
